NiftySwap lets you trade an arbitrary basket of tokens

that means writing code to work with arbitrary ERC-20, ERC-721 and ERC-1155 contracts.

we used the thirdweb SDK's Edition and Token methods to confidently handle all token types while moving fast

https://t.co/nXtp0IBZDM
(p.s. the NiftySwap contract's open-sourced https://t.co/eVVJK6Gtio)

We wrote a custom smart contract to facilitate the NFT+token trades that NiftySwap lets you perform.

To get this done in a week, we leveraged @thirdweb_'s smart contract library.

Alpha time: we used thirdweb's upcoming v2 smart contracts' "Multiwrap" ğŸ‘€

https://t.co/ob6WxN52md

The alchemy NFT/token api powers the core flow on https://t.co/39dpr6gKIB.

Instead of asking you to manually import the NFTs / tokens you'd like to bundle up and trade

the site presents you with the tokens you own, and you simply select the ones you'd like to bundle together

3. Many-to-many NFT trades

let's say @AdamLeeBG is a mega ETH bull and doesn't want to part with ether to pay the floor difference, for my cat.

No problem, I'll take more mfers for my cat then, and NiftySwap will let me https://t.co/VtgV0JsDG6

2. Cross-community NFT trades

my co-builder @AdamLeeBG likes the cats, and I like the mfers.

NiftySwap lets us trade into the communities we like, by trading my cat for the bundle of the mfer+floor difference

p.s. I would never leave the cats and Adam's a loyal mfer ğŸ˜¤ https://t.co/vYymJ7cssf

1. Trades within an NFT community.

At the moment, there's a ~2 ETH difference in the price of these apes.

If the owners of these 2 apes identify more with the other's ape, NiftySwap let's them trade apes directly, without:

- making any sales
- unsafe escrowing of NFTs https://t.co/9vt53y9CW1
